spfft
------------------------------------------
A 3D FFT library for sparse frequency domain data written in C++ with support
for MPI, OpenMP, CUDA and ROCm.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.1.7-1
  libfftw3-devel-3.3.8-1
  libfftw3_3-3.3.8-1
  libgcc1-10.2.0-1
  libgomp1-10.2.0-1
  libopenmpi40-3.1.6-1
  libspfft-devel-0.9.13-1bl1
  libspfft0-0.9.13-1bl1
  libstdc++6-10.2.0-1
  pkg-config-1.6.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.34+1git.de9c1b7cfe-1
  cmake-3.17.3-2
  cygport-0.34.0-1
  gcc-core-10.2.0-1
  gcc-fortran-10.2.0-1
  gcc-g++-10.2.0-1
  make-4.3-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/eth-cscs/spfft

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/eth-cscs/spfft/archive/v0.9.13.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack spfft-0.9.13-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./spfft-0.9.13-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/spfft-0.9.13-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/spfft-0.9.13-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libspfft0-0.9.13-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libspfft-devel-0.9.13-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

